Step1, setup of android databindings

Follow the guide on:
http://developer.android.com/tools/data-binding/guide.html

The important parts are:

Android Plugin for Gradle 1.5.0-beta3 or higher is required.

Add the dataBinding element to your build.gradle file in the app module.

android {
    ....
    dataBinding {
        enabled = true
    }
}

Use Android Studio 1.3 or later.

Step 2, bind a String to a TextView

Step 3, 

bind a handler to handle click events

Let visibility of a view depend on a boolean:
android:visibility="@{user.isAdult ? View.VISIBLE : View.GONE}"

Use a class to format your text:
<import type="com.example.MyStringUtils"/>
android:text="@{MyStringUtils.capitalize(user.lastName)}"









